-- Factbox: Five facts about new AIA head Tucker
-- 
-- Mon Jul 19, 2010 5:08am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/07/19/us-aig-tucker-idUSTRE66I0TB20100719

 

 (Reuters) - Former Prudential Plc ( PRU.L ) chief executive Mark Tucker was on Monday named by bailed-out insurer American International Group Inc (AIG) ( AIG.N ) as executive chairman and CEO of its Asian life insurance business, American International Assurance (AIA), replacing existing head Mark Wilson. 

 Following are five facts about Tucker: * Started adult life as a trainee professional footballer in Britain, making appearances for Wolverhampton Wanderers, Rochdale and Barnet. * Is a chartered accountant. First joined Prudential group in 1986, working initially in Prudential Portfolio Managers Limited. Was Chief Executive of Prudential Corporation Asia for a decade up until 2003. * Left Prudential in 2004 to join HBOS Plc as finance director. But returned as Prudential's CEO in 2005 and stayed in that role until 2009, when he quit the group. * Had eyed acquisition of AIA when he was CEO, but AIG did not proceed with the sale then. * Born on December 29, 1957 (Compiled by Muralikumar Anantharaman)